This paper deals with the design and optimization of wireless networks that are powered by both the electric grid and harvested renewable energy. As such, it is likely to fall under the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of optimization techniques and decision-making algorithms, which could place it under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of information theory and communication theory concepts, which could make it relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper involves the use of game theory and optimization techniques, which could place it under the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Mathematical Optimization (cs.MA) sub-categories, respectively.
